  description:`Chicago Blues Festival is the world's largest free blues festival — three days in Millennium Park and Grant Park that celebrate the music Chicago gave to the world, presenting legendary and emerging blues artists to 500,000 free attendees across multiple stages. Since 1984, the festival has been the centrepiece of Chicago's summer festival calendar and a celebration of the city's greatest musical legacy.\n\nChicago Blues is not merely a musical style — it is the foundation of virtually all popular music that followed. Rock and roll, R&B, soul and countless other genres descend directly from the electric blues developed on Chicago's South Side. The festival honours this heritage while presenting the contemporary blues scene in all its vitality and evolution.\n\nThe Petrillo Music Shell's main stage presents the festival's headliners — legends and contemporary masters — while the Front Porch Stage, the Blues Crossroads and the Lou Rawls Stage present a diversity of blues styles and emerging artists. The festival's free admission makes it one of the most democratic and beloved events in Chicago's calendar.\n\nFor food vendors serving Chicago's summer festival season, Chicago Blues Festival's 500,000 free attendees across three days provide exceptional volume and commercial opportunity — the free admission means no barrier to attendance, and the warm June Chicago days create strong appetite for the full range of food offerings.`,
  price_display:'Free',website:'https://www.chicagobluesfestival.us',
