  category:'festival',city:'Watkins Glen',country:'US',
  start_date:'2026-08-20',end_date:'2026-08-23',date_display:'20–23 August 2026',
  description:`Phish's multi-day camping festivals are among the most unique experiences in American music — immersive events where 50,000 devoted Phish fans camp together for four days of marathon improvisational performances, community activities and the extraordinary shared experience of Phish's musical universe. Curveball 2026 at Watkins Glen International returns to one of the great American music festival locations — the iconic New York state racetrack where Grateful Dead and The Band played to 600,000 people in 1973.\n\nPhish's jam-band format means no two shows are ever the same — the band's legendary improvisational ability means every performance is a unique musical journey, with songs that stretch from minutes to hours as the music evolves in real time. The camping festival format creates an extended community experience that Phish's devoted following (Phishheads) describe as transformative.\n\nWatkins Glen's beautiful Finger Lakes setting — rolling New York state hills, vineyards and the famous racing circuit — provides a spectacular backdrop for the camping festival. The Finger Lakes wine country's proximity means exceptional local wine, craft beer and artisan food are all available alongside the festival.\n\nFor food vendors and artisan producers, Phish festivals present one of America's most loyal and community-minded festival audiences — a demographic with strong spending power and genuine appreciation for quality food, local products and authentic artisan offerings.`,
