  start_date:'2026-10-31',end_date:'2026-10-31',date_display:'31 October 2026',
  description:`The New York City Halloween Parade is the world's largest Halloween celebration and America's greatest costume spectacle — a single night when 50,000 costumed marchers process through Greenwich Village as two million spectators line Sixth Avenue for the most creative, irreverent and spectacular street event in the American calendar.\n\nSince 1974, the Village Halloween Parade has been New York's great annual celebration of self-expression, creativity and community. The parade's puppets — some reaching five storeys in height — are among the most spectacular creations in street art; the performers, dancers, bands and costume-wearers who march represent the full diversity of New York's extraordinary creative community.\n\nThe parade's route through Greenwich Village — New York's historic bohemian neighbourhood — connects the event to a century of artistic and countercultural tradition. The surrounding streets fill with outdoor parties, street food vendors, pop-up bars and the general Halloween revelry of two million New Yorkers embracing the night.\n\nFor food vendors operating in the Greenwich Village area on Halloween, the NYC Halloween Parade creates one of the highest-traffic street trading evenings of the American year — two million people on the streets, a festive atmosphere and the crisp October air creating perfect conditions for warming food, festive drinks and seasonal specialities.`,
