  description:`The Great American Beer Festival is America's most important craft beer event — three days at the Colorado Convention Centre in Denver presenting 800+ breweries and 4,000+ beers to 60,000 craft beer enthusiasts. The GABF Awards are the Oscars of American craft brewing — winning a medal at GABF validates a brewery's quality credentials across the entire US beer industry.\n\nThe festival presents American craft brewing in its full diversity — from Colorado mountain lagers and West Coast IPAs to New England hazy IPAs, barrel-aged stouts, sour ales, session beers and the extraordinary range of styles that America's 9,000+ craft breweries have pioneered. The judged competition awards gold, silver and bronze medals across 100+ style categories, making GABF the most comprehensive quality assessment in American brewing.\n\nDenver's Mile High City setting — Colorado's beautiful autumn weather, the Rockies visible from the convention centre, the city's vibrant food and nightlife scene — creates an ideal festival environment for the autumn craft beer gathering. The city's own thriving brewing scene adds a local dimension to the national showcase.\n\nFor food vendors, artisan food producers and quality food businesses, GABF's 60,000 craft beer enthusiasts are among America's most engaged food-and-drink consumers — a demographic that applies the same quality standards to food as they do to beer, creating strong demand for premium, artisan food offerings.`,
