  description:`New York State Fair is one of America's great agricultural fairs — 13 days at the State Fairgrounds in Syracuse presenting the finest of New York State's agricultural, cultural and commercial life to over 1 million visitors each Labor Day season. Since 1841, the Great New York State Fair has been the annual gathering that celebrates everything New York State produces, creates and is.\n\nThe fair's agricultural competitions — livestock, poultry, dairy, produce and horticulture — celebrate New York's extraordinary farming heritage. New York State is one of America's most agriculturally diverse states, producing world-class wine, dairy (including the famous New York cheddar), maple syrup, apples, berries and specialty crops. The fair's food building presents the finest of these products in a marketplace of authentic New York quality.\n\nThe midway entertainment, grandstand concerts, demolition derbies and traditional fair attractions draw the full spectrum of New York State's population — from New York City families making the trip upstate to Central New York farming communities who have attended every year for generations.\n\nFor food vendors specialising in New York or American regional food, agricultural producers and artisan food businesses, the State Fair's 1 million visitors across 13 days provide sustained commercial opportunity alongside the cultural satisfaction of participating in one of New York State's most important annual traditions.`,
