  description:`The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo is the world's largest rodeo and one of America's greatest annual events — 20 days at NRG Stadium drawing 2.5 million visitors to the world's biggest celebration of Western heritage, agriculture and Texas culture. Since 1932, the Houston Rodeo has combined world-class livestock competition, championship rodeo and major concert entertainment into a singular American experience.\n\nThe rodeo's nightly performances at the 70,000-seat NRG Stadium present professional cowboys and cowgirls competing in bareback bronc riding, steer wrestling, team roping, saddle bronc riding, barrel racing and bull riding — the full programme of classic rodeo events performed at the highest professional level. The nightly concert following each rodeo has presented the biggest names in country, pop and Latin music — past performers include Taylor Swift, George Strait, Selena and Bruno Mars.\n\nThe livestock competitions — cattle, sheep, goats, pigs, poultry and more from across Texas and the US — are the heart of the agricultural fair. The carnival, BBQ cookoffs, educational programmes and cultural exhibitions extend the experience across the full 20 days.\n\nFor BBQ vendors, Tex-Mex food operators, Western craft producers and food businesses with Texas character, the Houston Rodeo is the most commercially significant single-location vendor opportunity in Texas — 2.5 million visitors with strong Western food culture and enormous appetite for authentic Texas fare.`,
