  description:`San Francisco's Chinese New Year Parade is North America's largest Chinese New Year celebration and one of the world's most spectacular Asian cultural events. The Golden Dragon Parade — featuring the famous 268-foot Golden Dragon carried by 100+ handlers — winds through the streets of San Francisco's historic Chinatown (the oldest in North America, established in 1848) each February to celebrate the lunar new year.\n\nOver 100 units participate in the parade — elaborate floats, marching bands, lion dancers, drum corps, acrobats, martial arts performers and the beloved Golden Dragon itself create a procession of extraordinary cultural richness and visual spectacle. Half a million spectators line the route, many wearing traditional Chinese New Year colours and filling the streets with the sound of firecrackers, drums and celebration.\n\nSan Francisco's Chinatown — centred on Grant Avenue, the oldest street in the city — transforms for weeks around Chinese New Year with special menus, decorations, temple ceremonies and community celebrations. The surrounding restaurants, bakeries and food vendors present traditional New Year specialities that attract both the Chinese community and the city's food-loving population.\n\nFor food vendors specialising in Chinese and Asian cuisine, artisan craft sellers and cultural product vendors, the San Francisco Chinese New Year celebrations represent the most significant Asian cultural commercial opportunity on the US West Coast.`,
