  category:'festival',city:'Telluride',country:'US',
  start_date:'2026-06-18',end_date:'2026-06-21',date_display:'18–21 June 2026',
  description:`Telluride Bluegrass Festival is America's most beautiful music festival — four days in the spectacular Colorado mountain box canyon where the world's finest bluegrass, folk and acoustic music is presented against a backdrop of 14,000-foot peaks that takes your breath away. Since 1974, Planet Bluegrass has created a festival of extraordinary intimacy and quality in what many attendees consider the most beautiful natural setting of any festival on earth.\n\nThe festival's Town Park venue — a natural amphitheatre in the floor of Telluride's canyon — provides seating for 10,000 with the surrounding peaks creating natural walls of extraordinary grandeur. When you look up from the stage to see mountains, sky and aspens, the experience transcends music and becomes something close to spiritual.\n\nThe programming spans the full range of American acoustic music — traditional bluegrass, progressive bluegrass, folk, country, Americana, singer-songwriter — with a curatorial eye for artists who truly belong in this particular place. Past artists include Alison Krauss, Del McCoury, Steve Martin, Sheryl Crow and dozens of acoustic music legends.\n\nFor artisan vendors and quality food producers, Telluride Bluegrass presents the highest-quality, most culturally engaged and most appreciative festival audience in America — a 10,000-strong community of music lovers for whom quality and authenticity in everything, from the music to the food, is non-negotiable.`,
